cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.CL, cs.LG

The paper deals with proof theory and logic, specifically first-order logic with nominal quantifiers. This suggests that the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the modelling of processes, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The use of the calculus of structures and novel techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computational Logic). Finally, the paper's focus on private names and non-commutative logic could also relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
